    <div class="article-teaser">
        The Central line will be suspended between Grange Hill and Newbury Park on the weekend of the 18/19 June 2005, due to track improvement works taking place between Grange Hill and Hainault.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<div class="pullquote right">
                        <p>
                            Customers are advised to allow an extra 15 minutes
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            <p>The works are being carried out by Metronet BCV.</p>
<p>A rail replacement bus service will operate between Grange Hill and Newbury Park calling at all intermediate stations.</p>
<p>Passengers travelling from Hainault, Fairlop and Barkingside should use the rail replacement service to/from Newbury Park and change there for the train service.</p>
<p>Passengers travelling from Grange Hill to Roding Valley stations will enjoy a direct service to central London.</p>
<p>Customers are advised to allow an extra 15 minutes to complete their journeys, especially those wishing to make the last train connections.</p>
<p>For 24-hour information on all London travel, please call 020 7222 1234 or visit <a href="http://tfl.gov.uk">TfL's website</a>. </p>
            <ul>
<li>Metronet Rail BCV is responsible for the maintenance and renewal of the Bakerloo, Central, Victoria and Waterloo &amp; City lines</li>
<li>TfL is investing &pound;10 billion over the next five years to improve and expand London's transport network, over half of that in the Tube.</li></ul>

     

        
        
        
